<p><i>potion</i> is a tiny, fast <a href="/wiki/Dynamic_programming_language" title="Dynamic programming language">dynamic</a>, <a href="/wiki/Stack-oriented_programming_language" title="Stack-oriented programming language">stack-oriented</a> computer <a href="/wiki/Programming_language" title="Programming language">programming language</a> with a <a href="/wiki/JIT_compiler" title="JIT compiler" class="mw-redirect">JIT compiler</a>, <a href="/wiki/Closure_(computer_science)" title="Closure (computer science)" class="mw-redirect">closures</a>, continuations and exceptions, a Lua-based VM and an Io-based object model built around <a href="/wiki/Message_passing" title="Message passing">message passing</a>, a <a href="/wiki/Metaobject" title="Metaobject">MOP</a> and <a href="/wiki/Mixin" title="Mixin">mixins</a>. It is technically a lexical-only <a href="/wiki/Lisp-1" title="Lisp-1" class="mw-redirect">Lisp-1</a> with two languages: one for code, one for data and it is written in under 10K lines of C.</p>
<p></p>
